parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A prolonged form of an otherwise obsolete verb; to talk, i.e. Utter words.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative Masculine 3rd Person Plural
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
Apart from, separately from; without. Adverb from chora; at a space, i.e. Separately or apart from.
From paraballo; a similitude, i.e. fictitious narrative, apothegm or adage.
A primary particle; but, and, etc.
Pertaining to self, i.e. One's own; by implication, private or separate.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To loose, release; I solve, settle, explain, interpret, decide. From epi and luo; to solve further, i.e. to explain, decide.
All, the whole, every kind of. Including all the forms of declension; apparently a primary word; all, any, every, the whole.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Pertaining to self, i.e. One's own; by implication, private or separate.
A learner, disciple, pupil. From manthano; a learner, i.e. Pupil.
